==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin, meaning "equivalent" and "night"

===Noun===
'''equinox'''

# the [[intersection]] of the [[ecliptic]] (apparent path of the sun) with the [[celestial]] [[equator]]. ''Vernal Equinox'' is the intersection that the [[sun]] crosses about March 21; ''autumnal equinox'' deontes the crossing point about September 21.

